  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section id="faq-section" class="pb-16 lg:pb-28 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-7xl py-16 sm:pt-24 flex flex-col items-center gap-y-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl flex flex-col gap-y-6 text-center">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center text-green-dark text-xs">
          <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8.228 9c.549-1.165 2.03-2 3.772-2 2.21 0 4 1.343 4 3 0 1.4-1.278 2.575-3.006 2.907-.542.104-.994.54-.994 1.093m0 3h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
          </svg>
          <p class="pl-1 font-bold">Import FAQ</p>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-heading">Common Import Questions</h3>
        <p class="text-base font-normal text-gray-500 sm:text-lg">
          Everything you need to know about importing from Pivotal Tracker.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-grow px-7 md:px-10 xl:px-2 py-4">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl sm:min-w-2xl">
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-1" id="import-answer-1" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-1" class="cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>Where do I find my Pivotal Tracker API token?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              Log into Pivotal Tracker, click your profile icon in the top-right corner, then select "Profile". Scroll down to the "API Token" section where you can view or create your token. Copy this token and paste it into LiteTracker's import tool.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-2" id="import-answer-2" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-2" class="group cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>How long does the import take?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              Most imports complete within a few minutes. Small projects (under 500 stories) typically finish in under a minute. Larger projects with thousands of stories and extensive comment history may take a few minutes. You can monitor progress in real-time during the import.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-3" id="import-answer-3" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-3" class="group cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>Can I import just one project first?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              Yes, absolutely! When you connect your Pivotal Tracker account, you can choose exactly which projects to import. We recommend starting with one project to test the process, then importing the rest once you're satisfied with the results.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-4" id="import-answer-4" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-4" class="group cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>What if something goes wrong during import?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              Our import tool is designed to handle errors gracefully. If an individual item fails to import, the process continues with the remaining data. You'll see a detailed log of any issues, and you can retry failed items. Our support team is also available to help with any import problems.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-5" id="import-answer-5" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-5" class="group cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>Is my data secure during import?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              Yes. All data transfers happen over encrypted HTTPS connections. Your Pivotal Tracker API token is used only during the import process and is not stored permanently. We never share your data with third parties, and you maintain full ownership of all imported content.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200">
            <input type="checkbox" name="import-answer-6" id="import-answer-6" class="peer sr-only">
            <label for="import-answer-6" class="group cursor-pointer flex w-full items-center gap-x-5 justify-between rounded-lg text-left text-xl font-normal text-black focus:outline-none p-6 peer-checked:[&_.open-icon]:hidden peer-checked:[&_.close-icon]:block">
              <span>Can I re-import if I need to update data?</span>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 open-icon block" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19" />
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 close-icon hidden" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="3" stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z"/>
                <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12" />
              </svg>
            </label>
            <div class="answer pt-2 pb-5 px-5 text-sm lg:text-base text-black font-light hidden peer-checked:block">
              You can run the import multiple times. If you import a project that already exists, you'll have the option to update existing data or create a new project. This is useful if you've made changes in Pivotal Tracker since your last import.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
